(124148, ' [b]ARMATIX IP1[/b]\n[img]http://img8.imageshack.us/img8/9646/arm2n.jpg[/img]\n[img]http://img13.imageshack.us/img13/8162/armagw.jpg[/img]\n\nThis high-tech gun belonged to Armatix. The German firm has an electronic safety that automatically disables the pistol when it’s not within a few inches of a custom wristwatch. The watch sends a wireless arming signal to the gun. If the gun is picking up a signal from the watch, a green LED on the back lights up. Try squeezing the handle without wearing the watch, and you will see a red warning light. Anyone can pick up a limited edition version of the pistol for about[b] 7,000 euro[/b] , which is pretty steep for a .22cal plinker.\n\n.22 LR calibre, 10 round magazine\nelectronic magazine disconnect\ndifferent operating modes\nan operating distance of up to 15 inches\nintegrated grip and drop safety\ncolor-coded operating mode, patented mechatronic interface for, e.g. camera control and target acquisition control modules.', ''),
